cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper presents a new framework for applying deep neural networks to denoising without requiring additional training data. This involves devising pseudo-labels and a novel objective function to train the DNN as a discrete denoiser. This work involves machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE).
